  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-a689dac9796f",
  "content": "### Task 3.5: Wire new checks into the Reasoner's `run` method\n\n\n```rust\nCheckType::MisplacedDoc => {\n    if let Some(ref rules) = self.docs_rules {\n        findings.extend(check_misplaced_doc(&entries, rules));\n    }\n},\nCheckType::CoverageGap => {\n    findings.extend(check_coverage_gap(&entries));\n},\nCheckType::TemporalContradiction => {\n    let threshold = 0.85; // same as merge similarity_threshold\n    findings.extend(check_temporal_contradiction(&entries, threshold));\n},\n```\n\n`MisplacedDoc` is a no-op if `docs_rules` is `None` (graceful degradation for non-workspace configs). `CoverageGap` is deterministic (no LLM needed). `TemporalContradiction` uses embeddings from stored entries (no live inference needed — entries already have embeddings).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run full reasoner tests**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-kernel reasoner -- --nocapture`\nExpected: All tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/reasoner.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(reasoner): wire new docs checks into Reasoner dispatch\"\n```\n\n---\n",
